author: Duncan Lindsay For Metro.Co.Uk
title: EastEnders airs a car crash horror for Dot but what comes next? | Metro News
text:
Duncan Lindsay for Metro.co.uk Thursday 23 Feb 2017 7:56 pm (Picture: BBC) 
EastEnders viewers have been left fearing for the safety of Dot Branning in dramatic scenes which saw her swerve her car into oncoming traffic before driving off of the road. As the vehicle ground to a halt on the verge, fans were wondering what the consequences might be for Dot. 
The pensioner, who has been struggling with her eyesight recently, took Matthew for a trip to the garden centre but the day took an unpleasant turn when, distracted by a sat-nav, Dot lost control of the car. (Picture: BBC) 
Thankfully, she didn’t crash into any other vehicles on the road but the incident is likely to have been terrifying for Dot and Matthew – and Jack Branning is bound to be upset with her for putting his son at risk. (Picture: BBC) 
Will the accident lead to Dot losing her driving license – and might it also prompt her to take her ailing sight more seriously moving forward? (Picture: BBC) 
Or might the guilt and the fear of what has happened lead to Dot going back into her shell? 
— BBC EastEnders (@bbceastenders) February 23, 2017 
EastEnders continues on Friday 24th February at 8pm on BBC One.
